I"Ïp<p>I am going to go step by step with the 80k blog and see where it takes me. I see there are lot of great points, amazingly evidence based. I would like to read about it and summarize the contents to my liking. Based on the old articles, it is clear to us that we want to use our time in the best way possible to create as much as impact as possible. This could mean donating 10k euros a year or 100k $ a year based on what is possible and high impact.</p>

<h3 id="you-can-be-wrong">You can be wrong</h3>

<p>Deep down you don‚Äôt know what you want to do. We make wrong decisions all the time.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>We are bad at predicting what will make us happy</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <p>It turns out we‚Äôre even bad at remembering how satisfying different experiences were</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <p>Some people imagine that the answer (to life) involves discovering their passion through a flash of insight, while others think that the key elements of their dream job are that it be easy and highly paid. - <a href="https://80000hours.org/career-guide/job-satisfaction/#dont-aim-for-low-stress">80h hrs</a></p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <p>We‚Äôve reviewed two decades of research into the causes of a satisfying life and career, drawing on over 60 studies, and we didn‚Äôt find much evidence for these views.- <a href="https://80000hours.org/career-guide/job-satisfaction/#dont-aim-for-low-stress">80h hrs</a></p>
</blockquote>

<p>Boom! Passion and ‚Äòwhat makes you happy‚Äô and the Robin Sharma type of advice can go straight into the bin.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>You‚Äôre passion can lead you astray - <a href="https://80000hours.org/career-guide/job-satisfaction/#dont-aim-for-low-stress">80h hrs</a></p>
</blockquote>

<p>You might want to become an ice cream vendor or a bus driver when you were young or even now. But there is no telling that you will be able to create the impact you need</p>

<h3 id="dream-job">Dream job</h3>

<p>A dream job would have the <a href="https://80000hours.org/career-guide/job-satisfaction/#dont-aim-for-low-stress">following</a>:</p>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>You would be working on something you are good at</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Your work would have direct(saving lives directly) or indirect impact (donations)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="/Mathivanan-2.html">Flow</a> while working; lack of major negatives (unfair pay); supportive colleagues</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Moderate amount of stress associated with you being in Flow can exist.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<h3 id="shaking-the-foundation-of-everything-you-know">Shaking the foundation of everything you know?</h3>

<p>Developing skill seems to be what I should focus on. Theoretically, I could be good at anything provided I practice and have the space to practice. So right now I guess this means to look for work in industries where I can create the maximum impact for the world over the 80k work hours of my life.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>the evidence suggests that money and avoiding stress aren‚Äôt that important.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Money might be important to us to create larger impact, but it‚Äôs a relief to know that stress might not be as serious as I think.</p>

